==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Drum winding
<hw>Drum winding</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A method of armature
winding in which the wire is wound upon the outer surface of a cylinder
or drum from end to end of the cylinder; -- distinguished from
<contr>ring winding</contr>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

